    },
    {
      "id": "s2-42",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "chmod 600",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod 600 example.txt\n$ chmod u=rw,g=,o= example.txt\n$ chmod a+rwx,u-x,g-rwx,o-rwx example.txt"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-43",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "chmod 664",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod 664 example.txt\n$ chmod u=rw,g=rw,o=r example.txt\n$ chmod a+rwx,u-x,g-x,o-wx example.txt"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-44",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "chmod 777",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod 777 example.txt\n$ chmod u=rwx,g=rwx,o=rwx example.txt\n$ chmod a=rwx example.txt"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-45",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Symbolic mode",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "Deny execute permission to everyone."
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-46",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Symbolic mode",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod a-x chmodExampleFile.txt"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-47",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Symbolic mode",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "Allow read permission to everyone."
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-48",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Symbolic mode",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod a+r chmodExampleFile.txt"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-49",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Symbolic mode",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "Make a file readable and writable by the group and others."
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-50",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Symbolic mode",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod go+rw chmodExampleFile.txt"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-51",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Symbolic mode",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "Make a shell script executable by the user/owner."
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-52",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Symbolic mode",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod u+x chmodExampleScript.sh"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-53",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Symbolic mode",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "Allow everyone to read, write, and execute the file and turn on the set group-ID."
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-54",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Symbolic mode",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod =rwx,g+s chmodExampleScript.sh"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-55",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Removing Permissions",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "In order to remove read write permissions given to a file, use the following syntax:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-56",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Removing Permissions",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod o-rw example.txt"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-57",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Removing Permissions",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "For our file example.txt, we can remove read write permissions using chmod for group by running the following command:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-58",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Removing Permissions",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod  g-rx example.txt"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-59",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Removing Permissions",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "To remove chmod read write permissions from the group while adding read write permission to public/others, we can use\nthe following command:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-60",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Removing Permissions",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod g-rx, o+rx example.txt"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-61",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Removing Permissions",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "But, if you wish to remove all permissions for group and others, you can do so using the go= instead:"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-62",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Removing Permissions",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod go= example.txt"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-63",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "Executable",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod +x ~/example.py\n$ chmod u+x ~/example.py\n$ chmod a+x ~/example.py"
    },
    {
      "id": "s2-64",
      "sectionId": "s2",
      "title": "chmod 754",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "shell",
      "code": "$ chmod 754 foo.sh\n$ chmod u=rwx,g=rx,o=r foo.sh"
    },
    {
      "id": "s3-65",
      "sectionId": "s3",
      "title": "SSH Permissions",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "```shell script\n$ chmod 700 ~/.ssh\n$ chmod 600 ~/.ssh/authorized_keys\n$ chmod 600 ~/.ssh/id_rsa\n$ chmod 600 ~/.ssh/id_rsa.pub\n$ chmod 400 /path/to/access_key.pem"
    },
    {
      "id": "s3-66",
      "sectionId": "s3",
      "title": "SSH Permissions",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\n### Web Permissions\n\n```shell script\n$ chmod -R 644 /var/www/html/\n$ chmod 644 .htaccess\n$ chmod 644 robots.txt\n$ chmod 755 /var/www/uploads/\n$ find /var/www/html -type d -exec chmod 755 {} \\;"
    },
    {
      "id": "s3-67",
      "sectionId": "s3",
      "title": "Batch Change",
      "kind": "text",
      "body": "```shell script\n$ chmod -R 644 /your_path\n$ find /path -type d -exec chmod 755 {} \\;\n$ find /path -type f -exec chmod 644 {} \\;"
    },
    {
      "id": "s3-68",
      "sectionId": "s3",
      "title": "Batch Change",
      "kind": "code",
      "lang": "",
      "code": "\nSee: [Command Substitution](https://tldp.org/LDP/abs/html/commandsub.html)\n\n## Also see\n\n- [Modify File Permissions with chmod](https://www.linode.com/docs/guides/modify-file-permissions-with-chmod/)\n  _(linode.com)_"
    }
  ],
